A transparent Layer-2 de-jitter / re-pacing relay for a Roland REAC
(EtherType 0x8819) stream carried over a bursty Wi-Fi / WDS path, plus its
OpenWrt packaging and LuCI app. The daemon buffers the master broadcast and
re-emits it on a recovered, constant cadence to the local stagebox, so a
clock-slave stagebox stays locked. It does NOT decode REAC audio, reorder
bytes, or tag VLANs — it relays whole Layer-2 frames. The VLAN trunk and
gretap fabric are the separate reac-transport package.

## Third-party code and references

This package embeds no third-party code. reac_repacer.c and pacer_probe.c are
an original implementation; the relay is protocol-agnostic and carries no
audio-format decode or wire-framing logic.

REAC's EtherType (0x8819) is referenced only as an interoperability datum,
used to recognise the frames to relay. Interface facts of this kind are not
copyrightable (originally reverse-engineered by the per-gron/reacdriver project
and others); no third-party code is copied and no third-party copyright
attaches.
